SENTENCE a related concept of thinking was developed by william james .
SENTENCE it's called ideomotor action .
SENTENCE ideomotor action is an activity that occurs without our noticing it ,  without our being aware of it .
SENTENCE i'll give you one simple example .
SENTENCE if you think of locations ,  there tends to be eye movement that occurs with your thinking about that location .
SENTENCE in particular ,  from where we're sitting ,  imagine that you're asked to think of our university library .
SENTENCE well ,  if you close your eyes and think of the library ,  and if you're sitting directly facing me ,  then according to this notion ,  your eyeballs will move slightly to the left ,  to your left ,   cause the library's in that general direction .
SENTENCE james and others said that this is an idea leading to a motor action ,  and that's why it's called  ideomotor action  an idea leads to motor activity .
SENTENCE if you wish to impress your friends and relatives ,  you can change this simple process into a magic trick .
